description: Number T(n,k) of self-avoiding planar walks of length k starting at (0,0), ending at (n,0), remaining in the first quadrant and using steps (0,1), (1,0), (1,1), (-1,1), and (1,-1) with the restriction that (0,1) is never used below the diagonal and (1,0) is never used above the diagonal; triangle T(n,k), n>=0, n<=k<=n*(n+3)/2, read by rows.
